message:
agent2: I already landed deep-merge logic in Features.update() (current on-disk version). It's not a one-liner delegating to super().update() — it iterates iterable.keys()/kwds and calls a new helper self._merged_value(key, value) which merges into an existing dict/Features/Sequence(dict) in place, else assigns normally; each assignment still goes through self[key]=... (i.e. __setitem__), so if your decorator wraps __setitem__/other dict-mutator methods it should already recompute _column_requires_decoding without needing update() itself decorated. If you still want @keep_features_dicts_synced on update() specifically, please apply the decorator to the method as I've written it (don't replace the body with a bare super().update() call, that would drop the deep-merge). Current update() body:

def update(self, iterable, **kwds):
    if hasattr(iterable, 'keys'):
        for key in iterable.keys():
            self[key] = self._merged_value(key, iterable[key])
    else:
        for key, value in iterable:
            self[key] = self._merged_value(key, value)
    for key in kwds:
        self[key] = self._merged_value(key, kwds[key])

Let me know if that works for you or if you need something different.
